info on this great image format.


There are NO WARRANTIES.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements "Requirements"

Needed:
- DT2RGFX from the IFF RGFX datatype package by Achim Stegemann.
  You can find it on AmiNet

Recommended:
- Directory Opus Magellan. You will get a progress gauge with it! ;-)

@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation "Installation"

Copy the script to »SYS:REXX«.

To set it up in Opus, just make a button or define a context menu entry in
your picture filetype that calls my script like (see @{"Usage" LINK usage} section
for more info):

ARexx SYS:Rexx/bild2rgfx.rexx GZIP NODELETE {Qp} {f}

Make sure the IFF RGFX datatype package is installed correctly and DT2RGFX
is in the command path.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage "Usage"

Throw some images at it!

Arguments of the ARexx script »bild2rgfx.rexx«:

bild2rgfx.rexx COMPRESSION DELETEMODE OPUSPORT FILES\M

COMPRESSION = XPK compression mode. I recommend GZIP.
DELETEMODE  = DELETE:  Deletes the source files after conversion. It
                       checks for the return code of DT2RGFX to detect
                       failed conversions. In this case it doesn't
                       delete the source file.

              NODELETE: guess what

OPUSPORT    = ARexx port name of Directory Opus. When calling the script
              from Opus use »{Qp}« to sent the ARexx port name.

              Use »NONE« when it should not use DOpus.

FILES\M     = Names of the images to converts. Quote them when they
              contain spaces.

              When using bild2rgfx from Opus just use »{F}« for that.

Example:    bild2rgfx.rexx GZIP NODELETE NONE image.ilbm

Arguments of the AmigaDOS script »bild2rgfx.bat«:

FILEPATTERN = Pattern for the files to convert.

Example     bild2rgfx.bat #?

@ENDNODE Usage

